Bug to close out newsgroup discussion - details below - subjest says it all.

I've only spent a little time on the VE so far, and am working on some
specific objectives, but I can't get past square one if I elect to use J9.

I like to be lazy in my use of J9.  I state J9 for my development instance
of Eclipse (-vmargs -Xj9) and I usually customize my JRE settings
(Prefs>Java>Installed JREs) to have -Xj9 added as a default vmarg so I
don't have to say so on each and every launch config for testing.

Just built a new 3.0.1 based development config with lots of goodies
including the VE and its associated partners GEF/EMF.  

First glance it was working fine.  Then I go and add my -Xj9 default. 
Once that has been added and used (launched a test instance of the
workbench), all subsequent opens of a VE editor fail (msgs at the end).

After a few testing cycles and leaps of guess-work I figured out that it
is the default use of J9.  Seems this is changing how your vms are spun up
and this causes trouble.   Shutdown/restart is no help.  I have to remove
the default vmarg, shutdown/restart, and return to the 'old' way of adding
-Xj9 to each/every launch config.

Is this a known issue?  It is very repeatable.

This is the shortest message set in the .log - there are longer ones as
well (let me know if you want those too).
